  "time_ut": 1657871477,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7 \u0d85\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"If a stable government is not appointed, the country will become inactive\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe warned that if a stable government in Sri Lanka is not formed soon, the country may become dysfunctional.",
        "Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said while participating in the BBC News Night program that there is great uncertainty whether Sri Lanka will be able to find enough foreign exchange to import fuel in the future.",
        "Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said that the progress of the negotiations to obtain an aid program from the International Monetary Fund depends on the appointment of a stable government.",
        "Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said that although the Central Bank will be able to provide financial facilities for at least 3 diesel ships and one or two petrol ships until the end of this month, there is great uncertainty whether it will be able to provide sufficient foreign exchange to pay for petroleum products.",
        "Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe pointed out that if sufficient foreign exchange is not found to pay for petroleum products, then a situation similar to the closure of the country may arise in Sri Lanka. Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said that there is a need for a president, prime minister and a cabinet that can make decisions. Mr. Weerasinghe said that if there is no such mechanism, the people will have to suffer.",
        "Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe pointed out that although Sri Lanka hopes to make positive progress in the debt restructuring negotiations, it also depends on how quickly a stable government is formed."
      ],
